keyValuePair.Value: Well beaten over the two games, what positives can you take?
Your team's been well beaten over the two legs and you're already out of the competition. What can you learn from the experience?
We just weren't good enough.
%1s looked at a different level to us in both games. We can't complain about the result. We have to look at ourselves now and see where we're short and how we can try to improve.
%1s are a much more experienced team.

We're a developing team. %1s have experienced players in key positions and that's why they've beaten us. Look at how settled and assured they are at the back. We struggled to get ourselves into decent attacking positions at any point in the game today.
The boys did all they could.

We've gone out of the %1s to a very good team. Of course we have to look at ourselves. They're dangerous enough without us presenting them with easy chances. But let's be positive. This is a team that's still developing and we did a lot of things well today. There's better to come in the future, that's for sure.
You're out after two defeats. Could you have approached this tie differently?
%1s are through to the next round after beating you comfortably home and away. Obviously they're a very good side but could you have taken a different approach? Did you make it easy for them?
We have to recover from this.

We'll look at what happened and work out why the lads weren't able to create enough from an attacking point of view. You have to give credit to the opposition. They put in two very professional performances and deserved to go through. But we have to recover from this. We can improve, I'm sure.

We'll look at what happened and work out why the lads weren't able to create enough from an attacking point of view. You have to give credit to the opposition. They put in two very professional performances and deserved to go through. But we have to recover from this. We can improve, I'm sure.
What can I say? %1s were the better team.
We have to accept that we were up against a better team here. %1s just didn't let us play in either game. We never really looked like we'd be good enough to go through.
We have to be more competitive.
We have to be more competitive.

We couldn't match the for quality but, at the very least, I want to see %1s compete. We looked inhibited, overawed. If you're not prepared to go toe to toe with your opponents, especially against the good teams, you're going to suffer. And we did.

We couldn't match the for quality but, at the very least, I want to see %1s compete. We looked inhibited, overawed. If you're not prepared to go toe to toe with your opponents, especially against the good teams, you're going to suffer. And we did.
You've missed out. What went wrong?
It's been such an impressive run to this stage of the competition but %1s have beaten you twice and are through to the Final. Why were your boys so disappointing in these two games?
We have to learn to manage expectations.
We have to learn to manage expectations.

I believe in this team and I thought we could reach the Final. Maybe they couldn't cope with the sense of expectation. We were all desperate to win and maybe I should have focused more on our defensive shape and on making us difficult to beat. Let's make sure we learn from this.

I believe in this team and I thought we could reach the Final. Maybe they couldn't cope with the sense of expectation. We were all desperate to win and maybe I should have focused more on our defensive shape and on making us difficult to beat. Let's make sure we learn from this.
We've been well beaten. Now we have to respond.
Missing out on the Final is a big disappointment for everybody. We didn't do ourselves justice in either game here. So now we have to find a way to respond. Let's come back stronger from this.
Missing out on the Final is a big disappointment for everybody. We didn't do ourselves justice in either game here. So now we have to find a way to respond. Let's come back stronger from this.
We didn't function as a team.

It was always going to be difficult, but we made life impossible for ourselves. Too many of our lads forgot the team plan and went off trying to win the game on their own. We needed to work together as a unit. Instead, we had individual players off trying to be heroes.

It was always going to be difficult, but we made life impossible for ourselves. Too many of our lads forgot the team plan and went off trying to win the game on their own. We needed to work together as a unit. Instead, we had individual players off trying to be heroes.
Your run in the competition's over. Can you have any complaints?
It's been a promising run in the competition but %1s were far too good for you over the two legs. Can you have any complaints about how this tie turned out?
%1s look like they could win the trophy!
My midfield players gave everything in both games but we couldn't get close to %1s's level. They deserve to go through. I can actually see them winning the trophy now.
My midfield players gave everything in both games but we couldn't get close to %1s's level. They deserve to go through. I can actually see them winning the trophy now.
There are always regrets.

We've been in good form and I thought we had a great chance of reaching the semis. But we came up against a team at the top of their game. Of course we'll have regrets, but at least we gave it our best shot.
Were we really up for the fight?

We were up against a better team but, at the very least, I want to see my players chasing and fighting for every ball. Instead, we sat back and let the opposition dominate us. Were we afraid of them? Or afraid of the occasion? Either way, it just wasn't good enough.
Are you surprised not to have qualified?
You were still in with a chance of qualifying going into the second leg, but %1s kept you at arm's length and the draw here puts them through. Did your boys let themselves down?
We gave it our best, I think.
We needed goals today but it seemed the ball just wouldn't run for us, no matter how hard we tried to make things happen. We're disappointed to go out but I saw plenty of positives from my team.
We'll come back stronger.
We had targeted this competition but we were unlucky to get drawn against such a powerful team. We just couldn't find a way past them today. We have to recover and focus on our next game now.
We're out because we didn't stick together.

Today was close. We just couldn't get the goals we needed. But we're out because we didn't stick together when we needed to in the first leg. We need to work on our organisation and discipline, for sure. We've let ourselves down.
After such a great run, why did you come up short here?
Your boys had looked so impressive on the way to the semi-final. But it's over. You weren't able to recover from that heavy defeat in the first leg. Where does the team go from here?
We gave ourselves too much to do.

The boys were all determined to make up for their mistakes in the first leg and I thought they were great today. But it wasn't enough. We'd given ourselves too much to do here to have a chance of reaching the Final.
We have to be better in the big moments.

In the first leg, we conceded at key moments and, today, we couldn't take our chances when we needed to. These are harsh lessons, being so close to the Final, but I can promise the fans we'll learn from this experience and improve.
It's about desire.

Semi-finals are often about who wants it more. We were on the brink of the Final but we were up against a team who just seemed to have greater desire and greater ambition. It was as if we didn't really believe in ourselves.
Was this tie won and lost in the first leg?
You weren't able to come back from your defeat in the first leg. Were you surprised your team couldn't get the goals you needed?
The boys did all they could.

Credit to the lads for giving it absolutely their best shot today. The defeat in the first leg meant we were chasing the game here. It's been a difficult experience. Looking at the game overall, you'd have to say we were good but probably not quite good enough.
We gave ourselves too much to do.
We respect %1s and knew it would be hard to come back after losing the first leg. I know for sure the lads believed they could do it but, in the end, we couldn't get the goals we needed.
We let ourselves down in the first leg.

We gave a really poor account of ourselves in the first leg. Of course I hoped we could achieve something special and come back, but we just didn't have quite enough. We gave ourselves too much to do.
Why have your team missed out on a place in the semis?
Why have your team missed out on a place in the semis?
You knew you had to get goals if you were going to turn this tie round. But, in the end, the defeat in the first leg was the difference. How big a blow is this for %1s?
You knew you had to get goals if you were going to turn this tie round. But, in the end, the defeat in the first leg was the difference. How big a blow is this for %1s?
There wasn't much in it.

The lads went for it today. We put up a fight and did everything we could to drag ourselves back into it. In the end, though, you'd have to say we're out because of the mistakes we made in the first leg. It was too big a hill to climb.
We're sorry for the fans.

I think our fans came ready to cheer us on to a great comeback. I feel bad for them. They saw the team give it a go and I hope they can feel proud of that display. But, in the end, we just weren't good enough to recover from the first leg defeat.
I feel we've let down our supporters.

We lost the first leg but I really thought we had a chance to turn this tie around. But we never got going here and really didn't show much as an attacking force. I'm disappointed. I think we've let our supporters down.
A brave effort from your %1s team. Why couldn't you find that extra goal?

It was always going to be difficult after your defeat in the first leg. How are you feeling now, though? Proud of your team's efforts? Or frustrated you couldn't find one more goal to complete the comeback?
Nobody can say we didn't put in the effort.

We knew we had to take the game to the opposition. The boys were very brave, very committed. But it never looked like being enough. We couldn't make the chances we needed to. After the first leg, we left ourselves with too much to do.
The boys showed character.

We're disappointed not to have qualified, that's for sure. I'm sorry we couldn't come back from our defeat in the first leg. But the team showed some character here. We have to recover from the disappointment now and move on.
We gave it away in the first leg.

Qualifying was a big target for us. Maybe we didn't deal with the pressure. We didn't do ourselves justice at all in the first leg defeat and the boys know that. Today was better, but we'd left ourselves with too much to do.

Qualifying was a big target for us. Maybe we didn't deal with the pressure. We didn't do ourselves justice at all in the first leg defeat and the boys know that. Today was better, but we'd left ourselves with too much to do.
Did you feel you did enough to reach the Final?
Did you feel you did enough to reach the Final?
It was bound to be hard after losing the first leg and it's %1s who are through to the Final. Did you expect more from your %2s side? Could they have done more to turn this tie around?
It was bound to be hard after losing the first leg and it's %1s who are through to the Final. Did you expect more from your %2s side? Could they have done more to turn this tie around?
Let's be better in future.

We had to put on a real performance today. I think our supporters thought we could come back and make the Final. I'm sorry we've let them down. We played with pride but couldn't get the goals we needed. We owe it to those fans to make sure we're better in future.
We're sorry to be missing out.

I think everybody connected with %1s can be proud that the boys got so far in a very difficult competition. Even so, we're disappointed to miss out. It was close, but we just couldn't find the goals we needed to go through.
It feels like we've missed a real opportunity.

I thought we'd be able to recover from that first leg defeat. But we lost our heads a bit, didn't we? Once we got in front, we needed to stay calm and wait for the chances to come. Instead, we lost our shape and went chasing the game. We should be more composed than that.

I thought we'd be able to recover from that first leg defeat. But we lost our heads a bit, didn't we? Once we got in front, we needed to stay calm and wait for the chances to come. Instead, we lost our shape and went chasing the game. We should be more composed than that.
Was that first leg defeat too much to come back from?
You can't ever criticise %1s for lack of fighting spirit. Your boys came very close to completing a famous comeback. How disappointed are you to have missed out in the end?
We have to learn to finish teams off.

The atmosphere at the game was amazing. It fired us up and I thought we'd be able to come back. And we so nearly did. One more goal and it would have been us going through. It's about knowing how to finish teams off.
I should have taken more risks.

Maybe I didn't take enough risks. I was worried the opposition would be able to catch us on the break and set us up to counter that. I should have gone with a more positive line-up. A bit more pressure and maybe we'd have got the goal we needed to stay in the %1s.
We all know why we're out.

Yes, we played well here. And it ended up a very close-run thing. But, when we look back, we know why we've been knocked out. You can't play like we did in the first leg of this tie and realistically expect to get through.
Could your team have done any more?

You got yourselves back into this tie against %1s but just couldn't find that bit extra to finish the job and go through. You must have regrets. Did that first leg defeat just leave you too much to do?
I thought we deserved better.

The team put in a fantastic effort. We wanted to put things right after the first leg. And we deserved to win the game, for sure. With a bit more luck and one more goal, it really could have been us going through.
We recovered some pride.
We know we let ourselves down in the first leg and, ultimately, that's cost us a place in the semis. But I was pleased with the boys tonight. We're disappointed but we've recovered some pride.
I was never confident we'd do it.

The defeat in the first leg was a real blow. We were so passive and never put the opposition under any pressure. We improved here but we weren't good enough overall. I don't think we ever really looked like getting the goals we needed to stay in the %1s.
You must be proud of the way %1s have made the Final?
You must be proud of the way %1s have made the Final?
%1s always seem to do it the hard way. I'm not sure many people saw you coming back from that defeat in the first leg. So reaching the Final must make you proud of your team?
%1s always seem to do it the hard way. I'm not sure many people saw you coming back from that defeat in the first leg. So reaching the Final must make you proud of your team?
We grabbed our chance.

I knew we could do something special in the %1s this season. And we needed something special here. The boys were fantastic. They came up with a real performance just when we needed it. We'll have to prepare properly to make sure we can find that kind of form again for the Final.
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

This was a fantastic achievement and we're very excited to get through to the Final. But we have to re-set now. That will be a completely different kind of game. We'll need cool heads out there. And a plan!
We got some pride back.

We were disappointed to lose the first leg. The lads knew they let themselves down in that game. But they're proud to wear the %1s shirt and they showed it here. Hope the supporters enjoyed it. What a comeback by the boys!
What a result! How did you inspire the turnaround?
To lose the first leg and then come back to win and go through is an incredible achievement. Your boys have done the %1s proud, haven't they? How did you mastermind that comeback?
We felt we had something to prove.
It wasn't just about managing to get through. We let ourselves down in the first leg. We came here feeling we had something to prove. I'm very proud of my team.
We had to qualify!

Progressing in the %1s is very important for the club's future. We made it difficult for ourselves after losing the first leg. But I think the boys' showed real hunger as well as quality here. We definitely deserved to qualify.
We came good when it mattered.

I don't know why we had to make it so difficult for ourselves! But, ever since losing the first leg, I've seen a real determination in the team. That hunger - and finding a bit of form when it really mattered -- is why we've gone through.
That's a great comeback. What inspired it?

You can't beat the %1s for drama. Your team has showed incredible character to come back after their defeat in the first leg. Did you know they had that performance in them? Or was it even more than you could have hoped for?
The boys were determined to go through.

We all knew we hadn't done ourselves justice in the first leg. I was looking to our more experienced players to stand up as leaders here today. They were great, kept driving us forward and we got our reward. I hope they can do the same in the semis.
We can be proud of that result.
Of course I'm pleased. The boys have done the club proud. But now it's about the semi. We've come so far on this journey. I want us to go all the way to the Final.
We don't know when we're beaten.

We're lucky to have a great spirit in the %1s dressing room. We lost the first leg but I could see how determined the boys were to put that right. Once we got our noses in front here, you just knew the comeback was going to happen.
Is that as good a comeback as you've ever been part of?
It looked like it was all over after the first leg. To turn in that performance today is quite an achievement. What inspired the comeback?
We got back to doing the simple things well.

That tells you all you need to know about how we can make %1s successful in future. Look at the performance the boys put on today. We were steady, we were brave, we were decisive. When we concentrate on doing the simple things well, anything's possible for this team.
I hope this is just the beginning.
The lads were a credit to the club today. They've shown themselves - and everybody else - what they're capable of. Let's hope this is the start of something special for this team.
Our spirit made the impossible possible!

It was a big ask, that's for sure. But the lads just weren't going to be denied today. They're honest players who never know they're beaten. And there's a great spirit amongst them. That's exactly the attitude that can take this team forward in future.
